cs like crumbles. But whether it's pickled, fermented, stewed or grilled, its potential goes far beyond desserts; here, we've looked at eight brilliant ways to use it in savoury dishes.\u003c\\/p>","teaser":"Distinctively sour and vibrantly pink, rhubarb is usually found at the heart of comforting classics like crumbles. But whether it's pickled, fermented, stewed or grilled, its potential goes far beyond desserts; here, we've looked at eight brilliant ways to use it in savoury dishes.","pageType":"FeatureArticle","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/how-to-cook-rhubarb-savoury-recipes","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/how-to-cook-rhubarb-savoury-recipes","image":{"randomStringId":"rxd41951f0fdb24dce9a6538ead08644b9","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/ygtds20l\\/holm-selects-7.jpg","alt":"","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2024-01-09T12:30:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2024-01-09T12:30:00Z","datePublished":"9 January 2024","score":0.86,"mobileTitle":"8 amazing ways to use rhubarb in savoury cooking "},{"biography":"                                                    \u003cp>After working with the likes of Gary Rhodes, Michael Caines and Gordon Ramsay, Stuart Collins set out on his own to open Docket No. 33, a small but perfectly formed restaurant in the beautiful town of Whitchurch in Shropshire.     \u003c\\/p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","id":54585,"nodeId":54585,"contentItemId":"cd4ecd66-02ce-44db-8682-769740d6b0dd","alias":"chefPage","title":"Stuart Collins","byLine":"","teaserHtml":"                                                    \u003cp>After working with the likes of Gary Rhodes, Michael Caines and Gordon Ramsay, Stuart Collins set out on his own to open Docket No. 33, a small but perfectly formed restaurant in the beautiful town of Whitchurch in Shropshire.     \u003c\\/p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","teaser":"After working with the likes of Gary Rhodes, Michael Caines and Gordon Ramsay, Stuart Collins set out on his own to open Docket No. 33, a small but perfectly formed restaurant in the beautiful town of Whitchurch in Shropshire.","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/stuart-collins","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/stuart-collins","image":{"randomStringId":"rx3ff9965f62bb4efcb436733e83fbb67d","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/mrpjzlnm\\/img88456.jpg","alt":"img88456.jpg","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2021-06-22T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2021-06-22T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"22 June 2021","score":0.86,"mobileTitle":"Stuart Collins"},{"chefName":"Chantelle Nicholson","id":63377,"nodeId":63377,"contentItemId":"ee3c6e3c-9d97-4118-ac9a-dd4fa3e0c23a","alias":"recipePage","title":" Rhubarb with cheesecake mousse and caramelised hazelnuts","byLine":"by Chantelle Nicholson","teaserHtml":"                \u003cp>Rhubarb is presented two ways in this pretty seasonal dessert – poached batons sit aside cubes of rhubarb jelly made from the poaching liquor. The scoop of cheesecake mousse is made with aquafaba (the liquid from tinned chickpeas) instead of egg white, and the crunchy caramelised hazelnuts bring a welcome crunch to the equation.                                                  \u003c\\/p>\n\n\n\n","teaser":"Rhubarb is presented two ways in this pretty seasonal dessert – poached batons sit aside cubes of rhubarb jelly made from the poaching liquor. The scoop of cheesecake mousse is made with aquafaba (the liquid from tinned chickpeas) instead of egg white, and the crunchy caramelised hazelnuts bring a welcome crunch to the equation.","course":"Dessert","difficulty":"easy","recipeType":"Chef","cookingTime":40,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/rhubarb-cheesecake-mousse-candied-hazelnuts-recipe","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/rhubarb-cheesecake-mousse-candied-hazelnuts-recipe","image":{"randomStringId":"rxc7863c9bf32c49b6927743696012f699","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/cnma1tz5\\/img86105.jpg","alt":" Rhubarb with cheesecake mousse and candied hazelnuts","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2020-03-06T15:57:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2020-03-06T15:57:00Z","datePublished":"6 March 2020","score":0.86,"mobileTitle":" Rhubarb with cheesecake mousse and caramelised ha..."},{"id":53242,"nodeId":53242,"contentItemId":"444ad7d8-cdb6-4b4c-9bc5-789c0d292c8d","alias":"collectionPage","title":"Italian cake","byLine":"Recipe Collection","teaserHtml":"","teaser":"","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatitalianchefs.com\\/collections\\/cake-recipes","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatitalianchefs.com\\/collections\\/cake-recipes","image":{"randomStringId":"rx4179bc08218c4ac8970b70f53d58d7fc","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/je5lpvdw\\/img78344.jpg","alt":"Cake","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great Italian Chefs","publishedDate":"2019-02-06T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2019-02-06T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"6 February 2019","score":0.84,"mobileTitle":"Italian cake"},{"id":63325,"nodeId":63325,"contentItemId":"96e2c71e-ab56-45fa-8ac3-37d0df52bc96","alias":"contentPage","title":"10 recipes to cook in February","byLine":"by Great British Chefs","teaserHtml":"                                                                                                                                                \u003cp>The weather is dreary, but hope is near – spring is just around the corner and February gives us some hope of good things to come with exotic fruits, the first of the year’s fish and delicious Pyrenean lamb.\u003c\\/p>                                        \n","teaser":"The weather is dreary, but hope is near – spring is just around the corner and February gives us some hope of good things to come with exotic fruits, the first of the year’s fish and delicious Pyrenean lamb.","pageType":"FeatureArticle","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/best-recipes-february","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/best-recipes-february","image":{"randomStringId":"rxa716e3516deb4330b3cce023f1a04fc3","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/aadhqpdu\\/img51842.jpg","alt":"image","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2019-01-30T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2019-01-30T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"30 January 2019","score":0.84,"mobileTitle":"10 recipes to cook in February"},{"biography":"                                                                                                    \u003cp>Few chefs cooking today are as exciting as Michael Bremner, who takes flavours from all over the world and distills them into beautiful small plates of deliciousness at his acclaimed restaurant in Brighton.                         \u003c\\/p>\u003cp>There’s no doubt that Brighton is home to one of the best food scenes in the UK, despite being within day-tripping distance to London. Over the past five years new restaurants, pop-ups, cafés and producers have helped shape the city into a fantastic place to eat out. But when you ask local chefs and owners who’s most responsible for this, most will point to one man in particular – Michael Bremner.\u003c\\/p>\u003cp>Growing up in a small town called Insch, just outside Aberdeen, Michael got into cooking the same way a lot of chefs do – by washing pots, then moving into the kitchen. ‘This was before the time of Jamie Oliver making cooking glamorous, so it was pretty brutal – especially for the first few years,’ he says. ‘One day a group of Michelin-starred chefs came in for dinner and one of them was Chris Galvin. My head chef Bob Ovington knew I was passionate about pastry at the time and organised a trial shift in London with Chris at The Orrery. I went there but I also wanted to go to Ibiza and work there for a season – when I was offered both jobs I told Bob I was going to take the one abroad, but he convinced me not to so I went down to The Orrery instead.’\u003c\\/p>\u003cp>\u003cbr>\u003c\\/p>                   \n\n\n\n\n\n","id":52101,"nodeId":52101,"contentItemId":"0fc55cba-a83b-4daa-8e01-0ecda44ac08d","alias":"chefPage","title":"Michael Bremner","byLine":"","teaserHtml":"                                                                                                    \u003cp>Few chefs cooking today are as exciting as Michael Bremner, who takes flavours from all over the world and distills them into beautiful small plates of deliciousness at his acclaimed restaurant in Brighton.                         \u003c\\/p>\u003cp>There’s no doubt that Brighton is home to one of the best food scenes in the UK, despite being within day-tripping distance to London. Over the past five years new restaurants, pop-ups, cafés and producers have helped shape the city into a fantastic place to eat out. But when you ask local chefs and owners who’s most responsible for this, most will point to one man in particular – Michael Bremner.\u003c\\/p>\u003cp>Growing up in a small town called Insch, just outside Aberdeen, Michael got into cooking the same way a lot of chefs do – by washing pots, then moving into the kitchen. ‘This was before the time of Jamie Oliver making cooking glamorous, so it was pretty brutal – especially for the first few years,’ he says. ‘One day a group of Michelin-starred chefs came in for dinner and one of them was Chris Galvin. My head chef Bob Ovington knew I was passionate about pastry at the time and organised a trial shift in London with Chris at The Orrery. I went there but I also wanted to go to Ibiza and work there for a season – when I was offered both jobs I told Bob I was going to take the one abroad, but he convinced me not to so I went down to The Orrery instead.’\u003c\\/p>\u003cp>\u003cbr>\u003c\\/p>                   \n\n\n\n\n\n","teaser":"Few chefs cooking today are as exciting as Michael Bremner, who takes flavours from all over the world and distills them into beautiful small plates of deliciousness at his acclaimed restaurant in Brighton.                         There’s no doubt that Brighton is home to one of the best food scenes in the UK, despite being within day-tripping distance to London. Over the past five years new restaurants, pop-ups, cafés and producers have helped shape the city into a fantastic place to eat out. But when you ask local chefs and owners who’s most responsible for this, most will point to one man in particular – Michael Bremner.Growing up in a small town called Insch, just outside Aberdeen, Michael got into cooking the same way a lot of chefs do – by washing pots, then moving into the kitchen. ‘This was before the time of Jamie Oliver making cooking glamorous, so it was pretty brutal – especially for the first few years,’ he says. ‘One day a group of Michelin-starred chefs came in for dinner and one of them was Chris Galvin. My head chef Bob Ovington knew I was passionate about pastry at the time and organised a trial shift in London with Chris at The Orrery. I went there but I also wanted to go to Ibiza and work there for a season – when I was offered both jobs I told Bob I was going to take the one abroad, but he convinced me not to so I went down to The Orrery instead.’","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/michael-bremner","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/michael-bremner","image":{"randomStringId":"rxfb3cd5e4f9904e558623f4ed8a236fd4","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/ukgibp2o\\/img75506.jpg","alt":"img75506.jpg","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2018-06-06T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2018-06-06T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"6 June 2018","score":0.84,"mobileTitle":"Michael Bremner"},{"chefName":"Martin Wishart","id":64180,"nodeId":64180,"contentItemId":"3a7ebfe3-a838-4418-9509-ddeb77648c9d","alias":"recipePage","title":"Rhubarb and crème fraîche tart ","byLine":"by Martin Wishart","teaserHtml":"","teaser":"","course":"Dessert","difficulty":"medium","recipeType":"Chef","cookingTime":210,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/rhubarb-creme-fraiche-tart","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/rhubarb-creme-fraiche-tart","image":{"randomStringId":"rx6e46c18dcd8a4525aae34d27afed5801","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/rcinqkw5\\/img25425.jpg","alt":"Rhubarb and crème fraîche tart ","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2015-08-19T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2015-08-19T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"19 August 2015","score":0.84,"mobileTitle":"Rhubarb and crème fraîche tart "},{"id":53304,"nodeId":53304,"contentItemId":"5b8d1839-5f80-4b89-a775-453d61d1c369","alias":"contentPage","title":"10 recipes to cook in January","byLine":"by Great British Chefs","teaserHtml":"                                                                                                                \u003cp>Christmas is but a distant memory and the new year festivities have ended, leaving us in the coldest month of the year. However, January adds a few exciting ingredients to the mix, including blood oranges, rhubarb and winter leaves like radicchio and castelfranco. Here's how to make the most of the month's produce.\u003c\\/p>\u003cp>\u003cbr>\u003c\\/p>                \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","teaser":"Christmas is but a distant memory and the new year festivities have ended, leaving us in the coldest month of the year. However, January adds a few exciting ingredients to the mix, including blood oranges, rhubarb and winter leaves like radicchio and castelfranco. Here's how to make the most of the month's produce.","pageType":"FeatureArticle","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/best-recipes-january","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/features\\/best-recipes-january","image":{"randomStringId":"rx6bf319ffdaca4321a98d9a417cf41a7d","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/xvujlk50\\/img73877.jpg","alt":"7 recipes to cook in January","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2018-12-31T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2018-12-31T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"31 December 2018","score":0.82,"mobileTitle":"10 recipes to cook in January"},{"chefName":"Chantelle Nicholson","id":64432,"nodeId":64432,"contentItemId":"4606c91d-0fe9-430b-ad06-e895533ef862","alias":"recipePage","title":"Rhubarb panna cotta, poached rhubarb, warm almond cakes","byLine":"by Chantelle Nicholson","teaserHtml":"                                \u003cp>This stunning vegan panna cotta recipe proves that dairy-free desserts can be just as delicious and comforting as their dairy-filled counterparts.                                        \u003c\\/p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","teaser":"This stunning vegan panna cotta recipe proves that dairy-free desserts can be just as delicious and comforting as their dairy-filled counterparts.","course":"Dessert","difficulty":"medium","recipeType":"Chef","cookingTime":100,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/vegan-panna-cotta-recipe","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/vegan-panna-cotta-recipe","image":{"randomStringId":"rx3ec698470d8b49fda18efbe7698b1611","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/2wvgvqnn\\/img74938.jpg","alt":"Rhubarb panna cotta, poached rhubarb, warm almond cakes","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2018-04-17T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2018-04-17T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"17 April 2018","score":0.82,"mobileTitle":"Rhubarb panna cotta, poached rhubarb, warm almond ..."},{"id":58050,"nodeId":58050,"contentItemId":"d4d8c680-7243-4fbd-99d6-b5bcc6b4c8b6","alias":"collectionPage","title":"Cake","byLine":"Recipe Collection","teaserHtml":"","teaser":"","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/collections\\/cake-recipes","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/collections\\/cake-recipes","image":{"randomStringId":"rx17bb7347e8304decbfae4ec8ce9fc088","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/e4apqzt5\\/img63540.jpg","alt":"image","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2015-04-21T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2015-04-21T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"21 April 2015","score":0.82,"mobileTitle":"Cake"},{"biography":"\u003cp>Emily Watkins came from a family where people had to fight for the kitchen – her mother and two sisters were all keen cooks. She remembers her childhood as one filled with experimentation and culinary disaster, telling the Good Food Guide she was always trying to cook, but 'would never listen to instructions – this is from age six or seven'. Her own passion for cooking was born out of greed: 'I always loved eating,' she says. Her mother manages a country house hotel in their home county of Dorset, so they were all roped into helping out in the kitchen. However, her family tried to dissuade her from pursuing a career as a chef, unsure of the realistic possibilities such a path offered – particularly for females. They instead steered her towards university and a degree in business, but her original aspirations never went away and post-graduation, after a torturous six months working in an office, she upped sticks for Italy.\u003c\\/p>","id":55785,"nodeId":55785,"contentItemId":"39d67c61-8ec7-4ba8-97ef-ff03243877dc","alias":"chefPage","title":"Emily Watkins","byLine":"","teaserHtml":"\u003cp>Emily Watkins came from a family where people had to fight for the kitchen – her mother and two sisters were all keen cooks. She remembers her childhood as one filled with experimentation and culinary disaster, telling the Good Food Guide she was always trying to cook, but 'would never listen to instructions – this is from age six or seven'. Her own passion for cooking was born out of greed: 'I always loved eating,' she says. Her mother manages a country house hotel in their home county of Dorset, so they were all roped into helping out in the kitchen. However, her family tried to dissuade her from pursuing a career as a chef, unsure of the realistic possibilities such a path offered – particularly for females. They instead steered her towards university and a degree in business, but her original aspirations never went away and post-graduation, after a torturous six months working in an office, she upped sticks for Italy.\u003c\\/p>","teaser":"Emily Watkins came from a family where people had to fight for the kitchen – her mother and two sisters were all keen cooks. She remembers her childhood as one filled with experimentation and culinary disaster, telling the Good Food Guide she was always trying to cook, but 'would never listen to instructions – this is from age six or seven'. Her own passion for cooking was born out of greed: 'I always loved eating,' she says. Her mother manages a country house hotel in their home county of Dorset, so they were all roped into helping out in the kitchen. However, her family tried to dissuade her from pursuing a career as a chef, unsure of the realistic possibilities such a path offered – particularly for females. They instead steered her towards university and a degree in business, but her original aspirations never went away and post-graduation, after a torturous six months working in an office, she upped sticks for Italy.","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/emily-watkins","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/emily-watkins","image":{"randomStringId":"rx7a17e16904f14c819ef0fedf9b330120","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/r0zmrcnb\\/img76653.jpg","alt":"Emily Watkins","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2014-12-10T00:00:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2014-12-10T00:00:00Z","datePublished":"10 December 2014","score":0.82,"mobileTitle":"Emily Watkins"},{"chefName":"Stuart Collins","id":64527,"nodeId":64527,"contentItemId":"d23e0fea-5aee-43c3-bf39-d7a0a2f89852","alias":"recipePage","title":"Yoghurt mousse with rhubarb and Turkish delight","byLine":"by Stuart Collins","teaserHtml":"        \u003cp>Rhubarb is paired with Middle Eastern flavours of yoghurt, pistachio and rose-flavoured Turkish delight in this wonderful dessert from Stuart Collins. All the elements can be made a day in advance, meaning you simply have to top the set yoghurt mousse with the rhubarb, rhubarb gel and Turkish delight before serving.                                                  \u003c\\/p>\n\n","teaser":"Rhubarb is paired with Middle Eastern flavours of yoghurt, pistachio and rose-flavoured Turkish delight in this wonderful dessert from Stuart Collins. All the elements can be made a day in advance, meaning you simply have to top the set yoghurt mousse with the rhubarb, rhubarb gel and Turkish delight before serving.","course":"Dessert","difficulty":"medium","recipeType":"Chef","cookingTime":50,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/yoghurt-mousse-rhubarb-turkish-delight-recipe","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/recipes\\/yoghurt-mousse-rhubarb-turkish-delight-recipe","image":{"randomStringId":"rx7a29fee9477f41429b16338183c1764c","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/bwjajb4d\\/img88441.jpg","alt":"Yoghurt mousse with rhubarb and Turkish delight","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2021-06-22T16:03:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":20,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2021-06-22T16:03:00Z","datePublished":"22 June 2021","score":0.8,"mobileTitle":"Yoghurt mousse with rhubarb and Turkish delight"},{"biography":"\u003cp>After investing everything he had into an old pub with a humble plot of land, Will Devlin's restaurant The Small Holding has become a true champion of farm-to-fork eating.\u003c\\/p>","id":55795,"nodeId":55795,"contentItemId":"040a5404-dfbf-4ab2-8e07-b166697220f8","alias":"chefPage","title":"Will Devlin","byLine":"","teaserHtml":"\u003cp>After investing everything he had into an old pub with a humble plot of land, Will Devlin's restaurant The Small Holding has become a true champion of farm-to-fork eating.\u003c\\/p>","teaser":"After investing everything he had into an old pub with a humble plot of land, Will Devlin's restaurant The Small Holding has become a true champion of farm-to-fork eating.","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/will-devlin","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/chefs\\/will-devlin","image":{"randomStringId":"rxe3ba0734ecbf432d8341516118aef9f3","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/0ubdodrv\\/img88218.jpg","alt":"img88218.jpg","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoint":false},"otherImages":[],"partitionName":"Great British Chefs","publishedDate":"2021-05-21T09:55:00Z","competitionEntered":false,"hasVideo":false,"isTheKitchen":false,"membershipTier":10,"isVisible":true,"isRenderedOnClient":false,"updateDate":"2021-05-21T09:55:00Z","datePublished":"21 May 2021","score":0.8,"mobileTitle":"Will Devlin"},{"id":58486,"nodeId":58486,"contentItemId":"5c10b928-b2da-4715-8f99-f13b559a1cac","alias":"collectionPage","title":"Spring","byLine":"Recipe Collection","teaserHtml":"","teaser":"","cookingTime":0,"url":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/collections\\/spring-recipes","link":"https:\\/\\/www.greatbritishchefs.com\\/collections\\/spring-recipes","image":{"randomStringId":"rx7472de4b8c7f49b8a8c843edde6b96a5","url":"https:\\/\\/media-cdn2.greatbritishchefs.com\\/media\\/pgalw1lv\\/img25725.jpg","alt":"Poached duck egg with English asparagus, cured ham and grain mustard dressing","useDoubleCrops":true,"hasFocalPoin